SIMPLE: florin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Florin
<hw>Flor"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>florin</ets>,
It. <ets>florino</ets>, orig., a Florentine coin, with a lily on it, fr.
<ets>flore</ets> a flower, fr. L. <ets>flos</ets>. See <er>Flower</er>,
and cf. <er>Floren</er>.]</ety> <def>A silver coin of Florence, first
struck in the twelfth century, and noted for its beauty. The name is
given to different coins in different countries. The florin of England,
first minted in 1849, is worth two shillings, or about 48 cents; the
florin of the Netherlands, about 40 cents; of Austria, about 36
cents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Florist</ent>⟦br⟧
